# - .env.test       (test environment variables)

# =============================================================================
# Vite Environment Variables Explained
# =============================================================================

# Vite has two types of environment variables:

# 1. SERVER-SIDE ONLY (process.env.*)
#    - Available only in server-side code (loaders, actions)
#    - Never exposed to the browser
#    - Use for sensitive data like API keys, database URLs
#    Examples: DATABASE_URL, STRIPE_SECRET_KEY

# 2. CLIENT-SIDE (import.meta.env.VITE_*)
#    - Available in both server and client code
#    - EXPOSED to the browser (visible in DevTools!)
#    - Must be prefixed with VITE_
#    - Use for non-sensitive configuration
#    Examples: VITE_API_URL, VITE_TIMEOUT

# Special Vite variables (always available):
# - import.meta.env.MODE ("development" or "production")
# - import.meta.env.PROD (true in production)
# - import.meta.env.DEV (true in development)

# =============================================================================
# How to Generate SESSION_SECRET
# =============================================================================

# Run this command to generate a secure session secret:
# node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"

# Or use online tools (but CLI is more secure):
# openssl rand -hex 32
